# SASS Installation Steps

## Step 1: Install Node.js version 20.16 using NVM
curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.39.7/install.sh | bash

## Step 2: Exit and reopen terminal
exit
# Then reopen terminal

## Step 3: Install and use Node.js version 20.16
nvm install 20.16
nvm use 20.16

## Step 4: Install SASS using npm
npm install -g sass

## Step 5: Verify installation
sass --version

## Note: The command provided in instructions (npm install sass -v 3.7.4) is incorrect syntax.
## The correct way to install a specific version would be:
## npm install -g sass@1.77.8 (for Dart Sass)
## or for the legacy Ruby Sass version 3.7.4:
## gem install sass -v 3.7.4
